SIMPLE: expound
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Expound
<hw>Ex*pound"</hw> <pr>(⟦ecr⟧ks*pound")</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos>
<vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos> <conjf>Expounded</conjf>; <pos>p. pr. &
vb. n.</pos> <conjf>Expounding</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[OE.
<ets>exponen</ets>, <ets>expounen</ets>, <ets>expounden</ets>, fr. L.
<ets>exponere</ets> to set out, expose, expound; <ets>ex</ets> out +
<ets>ponere</ets> to put: cf. OE. <ets>expondre</ets>,
<ets>expondre</ets>. See <er>Position</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To
lay open; to expose to view; to examine.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He <qex>expounded</qex> both his pockets.</q>
<rj><qau>Hudibras.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To lay open the meaning of; to explain; to clear of
obscurity; to interpret; <as>as, to <ex>expound</ex> a text of
Scripture, a law, a word, a meaning, or a riddle</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Expound</qex> this matter more fully to me.</q>
<rj><qau>Bunyan.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Expounder</ent>⟦br⟧
